Github user srdo commented on a diff in the pull request:

    https://github.com/apache/storm/pull/2465#discussion_r157349371

    --- Diff: external/storm-kafka-client/src/main/java/org/apache/storm/kafka/spout/KafkaSpout.java ---
    @@ -225,6 +237,23 @@ private long doSeek(TopicPartition tp, OffsetAndMetadata committedOffset) {
             }
         }

    +    /**
    +     * Checks If {@link OffsetAndMetadata} was committed by this topology, either by this or another spout instance.
    --- End diff --

    Sort of. I believe the storm id will be new every time you deploy a topology. According to the javadoc for getStormId it's the topology name + a nonce. So EARLIEST and LATEST will apply when you deploy the topology, but not when activating/deactivating the topology, and it won't apply if the spout crashes either.

